{"meta":{"updateDate":1691007959620,"pPcc":"SAT#Q","questionId":"1c2f50a6","skill_cd":"Q.B.","score_band_range_cd":2,"skill_desc":"Percentages","createDate":1691007959620,"program":"SAT","primary_class_cd_desc":"Problem-Solving and Data Analysis","ibn":"026410-DC","external_id":null,"primary_class_cd":"Q","uId":"d0284b76-678e-4bbe-b9df-06a0d5c9cbee","difficulty":"E"},"source":"legacy","detail":{"item_id":"026410-DC","section":"Math","prompt":"<p class=\"stem_paragraph \">During a sale, the original prices of all the items in a clothing store have been reduced by 20%. What is the sale price of a jacket with an original price of $50&nbsp;?</p>\n","answer":{"style":"Multiple Choice","choices":{"a":{"body":"<p class=\"choice_paragraph \">$12</p>\n"},"b":{"body":"<p class=\"choice_paragraph \">$30</p>\n"},"c":{"body":"<p class=\"choice_paragraph \">$36</p>\n"},"d":{"body":"<p class=\"choice_paragraph \">$40</p>\n"}},"correct_choice":"d","rationale":"<p>Choice D is correct. It&rsquo;s given that the original price of the jacket has been reduced by 20%. Multiplying the original price, $50, by 20% gives the amount, in dollars, that the price of the jacket is reduced by: <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"50 times point 2 0, equals 10\"></span>. Subtracting this value from the original price results in the sale price of the jacket: <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"50 dollars minus 10 dollars\"></span>, or $40.<p>Choices A, B, and C are incorrect and may result from a conceptual or calculation error.</p><p>&nbsp;</p></p>\n"}}}